4 mr075">By </em><a href="/authors/jannalevin/"><span class="byline__author uppercase kern light small">Janna Levin</span></a></div><p class="h6 o6 mv1 pv025"><em>July 3, 2024</em></p></div><div class="post__title__meta flex flex-wrap flex-items-start"><div class="post__title__excerpt wysiwyg p italic mb1 mt025 pr2 o4 theme__text">If you cover a surface with tiles, repetitive patterns always emerge — or do they? In this week’s episode, mathematician Natalie Priebe Frank and co-host Janna Levin discuss how recent breakthroughs in tiling can unlock structural secrets in the natural world.</div><div class="post__title__actions h5 mt025 flex-auto flex flex-items-center"><div class="comments-button mr05 flex flex-items-center theme__accent"><a href="#comments" class="flex flex-items-center pangram"><svg viewBox="0 0 50 50" enable-background="new 0 0 50 50"><title>Comment</title><path fill="currentColor" d="M9.4 4.2h31.2c8.6 0 9.4 7 9.4 15.6s-.7 15.6-9.4 15.6h-2.2l-.9 9.4-18.8-9.4H9.4c-8.6 0-9.4-7-9.4-15.6S.7 4.2 9.4 4.2z"></path></svg><div><span class="comments-button__count ml075 small mbold disqus-comment-count" data-disqus-identifier="138915 https://www.quantamagazine.org/?p=138915"></span></div></a></div><span class="o-divider mh075 relative"></span><div class="relative"><button class="bookmark-button mh05 flex flex-items-center theme__accent-hover" aria-expanded="false"><svg class="icon" viewBox="0 0 50 50" enable-background="new 0 0 50 50"><title>Save Article</title><path fill="currentColor" d="M2.1 0h45.8v50L25.5 37.5 2.1 50V0z"></path></svg></button><div class="q-tooltip hidden force-mobile-placement" style="width:130px;top:55px;margin-left:-65px"><div class="q-tooltip-content"><div class="q-tooltip-arrow"></div><div class="q-tooltip-inner" role="tooltip"><div class="h6t relative z1 uppercase kern--w mx025"><span class="small no-wrap">Read Later</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></section></section></div><figure class="lh-0 w-100P 